Test asserts unsigned headers get rejected. Covers all three bypass paths from diff.

```python
import pytest
from app.middleware.auth import AuthMiddleware, Unauthorized

class FakeRequest:
    def __init__(self, headers=None, cookies=None):
        self.headers = headers or {}
        self.cookies = cookies or {}

@pytest.mark.parametrize("headers", [
    {"X-Gateway-User-Id": "alice"},
    {"X-Gateway-User-Id": "alice", "X-Gateway-Signature": "deadbeef"},
    {"X-User-Id": "alice"},
    {},
])
def test_unsigned_identity_headers_rejected(headers):
    mw = AuthMiddleware(sessions={})
    req = FakeRequest(headers=headers)
    with pytest.raises(Unauthorized):
        mw.resolve_user(req)
```

Four cases: missing signature, bad signature, legacy header, no auth at all. All must raise. If any returns a User, regression reintroduced.
